modules.description: Provides operations to compare values for equality, compute hash values, and generate unique instances. Works with the abstract type `t` to ensure distinctness across invocations. Used to create unique identifiers in scenarios requiring deterministic uniqueness without external dependencies.

Provides runtime generation of extension constructors and exceptions, with type checking based on physical equality of constructors. Works with extensible variant types and exceptions, ensuring type consistency across marshalled data. Enables safe marshalling of dynamically created exceptions and variant types in distributed systems.

Provides operations to compare instances for equality, generate hash values, and create new unique instances. Works with the abstract type `t` representing distinct entities. Used to manage unique identifiers in concurrent or distributed systems where uniqueness and comparability are critical.
